{
  "texts": [
    "These residual connections are used to resolve the exploding gradient and vanishing gradient issues, which effectively enhance the accuracy of human motion intention prediction.",
    "The Res-LSTM model utilizes multiple residual layers in the LSTM model, and every layer has 64 configured units in the return sequence.The input layer effectively pre-codes the single 64 units in the LSTM layer.",
    "The Res-LSTM mechanism uses an auxiliary spatial shortcut connection in the LSTM structure to develop the temporal dependencies efficiently.The gating variables are validated by different characteristic equations, and they are listed below.Here, the inputs with time steps are presented as Pu and represented in Eq.",
    "( 6).Pu = σ (Ycpcu + Y f pfu-1 + Jp) (6)Forgot gate of the Res-LSTM model is offered as Gu and it is specified in Eq.",
    "Gu = σ (YcGcu + Y f Gfu-1 + JG)(7)The output gates are represented as Nu and it is given in Eq."
